HEADWORD: unhitch
<hw>un*hitch"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>hitch</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from being
hitched, or as if from being hitched; to unfasten; to loose; <as>as, to
<ex>unhitch</ex> a horse, or a trace</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

